searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"Pdf","doc":"The missing PDF library for Elixir.","ref":"Pdf.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - Pdf","doc":"```elixir\nPdf.build([size: :a4, compress: true], fn pdf ->\n  pdf\n  |> Pdf.set_info(title: \"Demo PDF\")\n  |> Pdf.set_font(\"Helvetica\", 10)\n  |> Pdf.text_at({200,200}, \"Welcome to Pdf\")\n  |> Pdf.write_to(\"test.pdf\")\nend)\n```","ref":"Pdf.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Page sizes - Pdf","doc":"The available page sizes are:\n\n - `:a0` - `:a9`\n - `:b0` - `:b9`\n - `:c5e`\n - `:comm10e`\n - `:dle`\n - `:executive`\n - `:folio`\n - `:ledger`\n - `:legal`\n - `:letter`\n - `:tabloid`\n - a custom size `[width, height]` in Pdf points.\n\nor you can also specify a tuple `{size, :landscape}`.","ref":"Pdf.html#module-page-sizes"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.cap_style/0","doc":"A code specifying the shape of the endpoints for an open path that is stroked.\n\n- :butt (default)\n\n  The stroke shall be squared of at the endpoint of the path.\n\n- :round\n\n  A small semicircular arc with a diameter equal to the line width shall be drawn around the endpoint and shall be filled in.\n\n- :square | :projecting_square\n\n  The stroke shall continue beyond the endpoint of the path for a distance equal to half the line width and shall be squared of.","ref":"Pdf.html#t:cap_style/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.cmyk/0","doc":"Specify a color by it's CMYK make-up.","ref":"Pdf.html#t:cmyk/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.color_name/0","doc":"Use one of the colors in the `Pdf.Color` module.","ref":"Pdf.html#t:color_name/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.coords/0","doc":"Most functions take a coordinates tuple, `{x, y}`.\nIn Pdf these start from the bottom-left of the page.","ref":"Pdf.html#t:coords/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.dimension/0","doc":"Width and height expressed in Pdf points","ref":"Pdf.html#t:dimension/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.height/0","doc":"The height in points","ref":"Pdf.html#t:height/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.join_style/0","doc":"The line join style shall specify the shape to be used at the corners of paths that are stroked.\n\n- :miter\n\n  The outer edges of the strokes for the two segments shall be extended until they meet at an angle. If the segments meet at too sharp an angle (as defined in section 8.4.3.5 of the PDF specs), a bevel join shall be used instead.\n\n- :round\n\n  An arc of a circle with a diameter equal to the line width shall be drawn around the point where the two segments meet, connecting the outer edges of the strokes for the two segments.  This pieslice-shae figure shall be filled in, producing a rounded corner.\n\n- :bevel\n\n  The two segments shall be finished with butt caps (see `t:cap_style/0`) and the resulting notch beyond the ends of the segments shall be filled with a triangle.","ref":"Pdf.html#t:join_style/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.rgb/0","doc":"Specify a color by it's RGB make-up.","ref":"Pdf.html#t:rgb/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.width/0","doc":"The width in points","ref":"Pdf.html#t:width/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.x/0","doc":"The x-coordinate","ref":"Pdf.html#t:x/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.y/0","doc":"The y-coordinate","ref":"Pdf.html#t:y/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.add_font/2","doc":"Add a font to the list of available fonts.\n\nCurrently only _Type 1_ AFM/PFB fonts are supported.\n\n```elixir\n\nfonts_dir = Application.app_dir(:my_app) |> Path.join(\"priv\", \"fonts\")\n\npdf\n|> Pdf.add_font(Path.join(fonts_dir, \"DejavuSans.afm\")\n|> Pdf.add_font(Path.join(fonts_dir, \"DejavuSans-Bold.afm\")\n```\n\nThe font can then be set with `set_font/3`.\n\nYou have to `add_font/2` all variants you want to use, bold, italic, ...","ref":"Pdf.html#add_font/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.add_image/3","doc":"Add an images (PNG, or JPEG only) at the given coordinates.","ref":"Pdf.html#add_image/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.add_image/4","doc":"Add an images (PNG, or JPEG only) at the given coordinates.\n\nYou can specify a `:width` and `:height` in the options, the image will then be scaled.","ref":"Pdf.html#add_image/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.add_page/2","doc":"Add a new page to the Pdf with the given page size.","ref":"Pdf.html#add_page/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.autoprint/1","doc":"Adds an autoprint action to the Pdf.\n\nThis is can be useful for generating a PDF that will automatically open the print dialog in a browser","ref":"Pdf.html#autoprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.background/2","doc":"Fill the current page background with a color.","ref":"Pdf.html#background/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.background/2","doc":"pdf |> Pdf.background(%{color: {0.95, 0.95, 1.0}})","ref":"Pdf.html#background/2-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.box/5","doc":"Render a box container at `{x, y}` with size `{w, h}`.\n\nSupports padding, margin, border, border_radius, and background.\nThe callback receives `(doc, %{x, y, width, height})` with the inner area.\n\nSize supports relative dimensions:\n- `:full` — 100% of the document's content area\n- `\"50%\"` — percentage of the content area\n- `number` — absolute points (default)","ref":"Pdf.html#box/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.box/5","doc":"doc\n    |> Pdf.box({50, 700}, {:full, 200}, %{padding: 10, border: 1}, fn doc, area ->\n      Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x + 5, area.y - 14}, \"Inside the box\")\n    end)","ref":"Pdf.html#box/5-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.build/2","doc":"Builds a PDF document.\n\n```elixir\nPdf.build([size: :a3], fn pdf ->\n  pdf\n  |> Pdf.set_font(\"Helvetica\", 12)\n  |> Pdf.text_at({100, 100}, \"Open\")\n  |> Pdf.write_to(\"test.pdf\")\nend)\n```\nis equivalent to\n```elixir\npdf = Pdf.new(size: :a3)\npdf\n|> Pdf.set_font(\"Helvetica\", 12)\n|> Pdf.text_at({100, 100}, \"Open\")\n|> Pdf.write_to(\"test.pdf\")\n```","ref":"Pdf.html#build/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.cleanup/1","doc":"No-op. Kept for backwards compatibility.","ref":"Pdf.html#cleanup/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.clip/1","doc":"Set the current path as a clipping boundary.","ref":"Pdf.html#clip/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.close_path/1","doc":"Close the current path by drawing a straight line back to the starting point.","ref":"Pdf.html#close_path/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.cm/1","doc":"Convert the given value from cm to Pdf points","ref":"Pdf.html#cm/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.column/5","doc":"Stack content vertically with fixed heights.\n\n`rows` is a list of `{height, callback}` tuples.\nSize supports relative dimensions (`:full`, `\"50%\"`).","ref":"Pdf.html#column/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.column/5","doc":"doc\n    |> Pdf.column({50, 700}, {:full, 400}, [\n      {50, fn doc, area -> Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Row 1\") end},\n      {80, fn doc, area -> Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Row 2\") end}\n    ], gap: 5)","ref":"Pdf.html#column/5-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.content_area/1","doc":"Returns the content area `%{x, y, width, height}` based on margins.","ref":"Pdf.html#content_area/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.cursor/1","doc":"Gets the current cursor Y position (vertical).","ref":"Pdf.html#cursor/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.cursor_xy/1","doc":"Gets the current cursor position as `%{x: x, y: y}`.","ref":"Pdf.html#cursor_xy/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.curve_to/4","doc":"Draw a Bézier curve from the current point through control points to the end point.\n\n```elixir\npdf\n|> Pdf.move_to({100, 100})\n|> Pdf.curve_to({120, 150}, {180, 150}, {200, 100})\n|> Pdf.stroke()\n```","ref":"Pdf.html#curve_to/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.debug_grid/2","doc":"Draw a debug grid overlay on the current page.","ref":"Pdf.html#debug_grid/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Pdf.debug_grid/2","doc":"- `:grid` — `:horizontal`, `:vertical`, or `:both` (default `:both`)\n  - `:area` — where to draw the grid:\n    - `:content` — inside margins only (default)\n    - `:page` — entire page (0,0 to page width/height)\n    - `:margins` — only in the margin zones (outside content area)\n  - `:spacing` — distance between grid lines in points (default `10`)\n  - `:color` — grid line color (default `{0.85, 0.85, 0.85}`)\n  - `:line_width` — grid line width (default `0.25`)\n  - `:labels` — show coordinate labels (default `true`)\n  - `:label_every` — show a coordinate label every N points (default `50`)\n  - `:info` — show page/margin info text (default `true`)\n  - `:margin_border` — draw the margin boundary rectangle (default `true`)\n  - `:cursor_line` — draw cursor Y position line (default `true`)","ref":"Pdf.html#debug_grid/2-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - Pdf.debug_grid/2","doc":"pdf |> Pdf.debug_grid()\n    pdf |> Pdf.debug_grid(%{grid: :horizontal, area: :page})\n    pdf |> Pdf.debug_grid(%{grid: :vertical, area: :content, spacing: 20})\n    pdf |> Pdf.debug_grid(%{area: :margins, color: {1.0, 0.9, 0.9}})","ref":"Pdf.html#debug_grid/2-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.delete/1","doc":"","ref":"Pdf.html#delete/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.export/1","doc":"Export the Pdf to a binary representation.\n\nThis is can be used in eg Phoenix to send a PDF to the browser.\n\n```elixir\n  report =\n    pdf\n    |> ...\n    |> Pdf.export()\n\n conn\n  |> put_resp_content_type(\"application/pdf\")\n  |> put_resp_header(\n    \"content-disposition\",\n    \"attachment; filename=\"document.pdf\"\"\n  )\n  |> send_resp(200, report)\n```","ref":"Pdf.html#export/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.fill/1","doc":"Fill the current drawing with the previously set color.","ref":"Pdf.html#fill/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.fill_and_stroke/1","doc":"Fill and stroke the current path.","ref":"Pdf.html#fill_and_stroke/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.horizontal_line/2","doc":"Draw a horizontal line at the current cursor position across the content width.","ref":"Pdf.html#horizontal_line/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.horizontal_line/2","doc":"pdf |> Pdf.horizontal_line()\n    pdf |> Pdf.horizontal_line(%{color: :gray, line_width: 0.5})","ref":"Pdf.html#horizontal_line/2-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.inches/1","doc":"Convert the given value from inches to Pdf points","ref":"Pdf.html#inches/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.line/3","doc":"Draw a line between 2 points.","ref":"Pdf.html#line/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.line_append/2","doc":"Draw a line from the last position to the given coordinates.\n```elixir\n  pdf\n  |> Pdf.move_to({100, 100})\n  |> Pdf.line_append({200, 200})\n```","ref":"Pdf.html#line_append/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.mm/1","doc":"Convert the given value from mm to Pdf points","ref":"Pdf.html#mm/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.move_down/2","doc":"Move the cursor `amount` points down.","ref":"Pdf.html#move_down/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.move_right/2","doc":"Move the cursor `amount` points to the right.","ref":"Pdf.html#move_right/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.move_to/2","doc":"Move the cursor to the given coordinates.","ref":"Pdf.html#move_to/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.new/1","doc":"Create a new Pdf document.\n\nThe following options can be given:\n\n:size      |  Page size, defaults to `:a4`\n:compress  |  Compress the Pdf, default: `true`\n\nThere is no standard font selected when creating a new PDF, so set one with `set_font/3` before adding text.","ref":"Pdf.html#new/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.on_page/3","doc":"Register a page template that runs on every new page.\n\nSupported template names: `:header`, `:footer`, `:watermark`, `:background`.\n\nThe function receives `(document, page_info)` where `page_info` is `%{number: n}`.","ref":"Pdf.html#on_page/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.on_page/3","doc":"pdf\n    |> Pdf.on_page(:header, fn doc, _info ->\n      Pdf.text_at(doc, {40, 820}, \"My Header\")\n    end)","ref":"Pdf.html#on_page/3-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.open/2","doc":"","ref":"Pdf.html#open/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.page_break/2","doc":"Insert a page break. Executes footer template on the current page\nand header/watermark templates on the new page.","ref":"Pdf.html#page_break/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.page_break/2","doc":"pdf |> Pdf.page_break()\n    pdf |> Pdf.page_break(:letter)","ref":"Pdf.html#page_break/2-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.page_number/1","doc":"Returns the current page number.","ref":"Pdf.html#page_number/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.picas/1","doc":"Convert the given value from picas to Pdf points","ref":"Pdf.html#picas/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.pixels_to_points/2","doc":"Convert the given value from pixels to Pdf points","ref":"Pdf.html#pixels_to_points/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.points/1","doc":"The unit of measurement in a Pdf are points, where *1 point = 1/72 inch*.\nThis means that a standard A4 page, 8.27 inch, translates to 595 points.","ref":"Pdf.html#points/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.rectangle/3","doc":"Draw a rectangle from coordinates x,y (lower left corner) for a given width and height.","ref":"Pdf.html#rectangle/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.register_style/3","doc":"Register a named style that can be referenced by atom in text/3, horizontal_line/2, etc.","ref":"Pdf.html#register_style/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.register_style/3","doc":"pdf\n    |> Pdf.register_style(:heading, %{font_size: 24, bold: true, color: :navy})\n    |> Pdf.register_style(:body, %{font_size: 12, color: :black})\n    |> Pdf.register_style(:accent, %{font_size: 12, color: :green})\n    |> Pdf.text(\"My Title\", :heading)\n    |> Pdf.text(\"Body text\", :body)","ref":"Pdf.html#register_style/3-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.register_styles/2","doc":"Register multiple named styles at once from a map.","ref":"Pdf.html#register_styles/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.register_styles/2","doc":"Pdf.register_styles(pdf, %{\n      heading: %{font_size: 24, bold: true, color: :navy},\n      body: %{font_size: 12},\n      footer: %{font_size: 8, color: :gray}\n    })","ref":"Pdf.html#register_styles/2-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.reset_x/1","doc":"Reset the cursor X position to 0.","ref":"Pdf.html#reset_x/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.restore_state/1","doc":"Restore a previously saved graphics state.","ref":"Pdf.html#restore_state/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.rotate/2","doc":"Rotate the coordinate system by the given angle in degrees.\nMust be used within `save_state/restore_state`.","ref":"Pdf.html#rotate/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.rounded_rectangle/4","doc":"Draw a rounded rectangle.","ref":"Pdf.html#rounded_rectangle/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.row/5","doc":"Distribute content horizontally in columns by weight.\n\n`columns` is a list of `{weight, callback}` tuples.\nSize supports relative dimensions (`:full`, `\"50%\"`).","ref":"Pdf.html#row/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.row/5","doc":"doc\n    |> Pdf.row({50, 700}, {:full, 80}, [\n      {1, fn doc, area -> Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Left\") end},\n      {2, fn doc, area -> Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Center\") end}\n    ], gap: 10)","ref":"Pdf.html#row/5-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.save_state/1","doc":"Save the current graphics state. Use with `restore_state/1` to isolate\ntransformations like rotation, translation, scaling, and opacity changes.","ref":"Pdf.html#save_state/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.scale/2","doc":"Scale the coordinate system by {sx, sy}.\nMust be used within `save_state/restore_state`.","ref":"Pdf.html#scale/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_author/2","doc":"Sets the author in the PDF information section.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_author/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_creator/2","doc":"Sets the creator in the PDF information section.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_creator/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_cursor/2","doc":"Set the cursor Y position.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_cursor/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_cursor_x/2","doc":"Set the cursor X position.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_cursor_x/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_dash/3","doc":"Set the dash pattern for stroking operations.\n\n- `set_dash(doc, [3, 3], 0)` — dashed line (3 on, 3 off)\n- `set_dash(doc, [6, 2], 0)` — long dash\n- `set_dash(doc, [], 0)` — reset to solid","ref":"Pdf.html#set_dash/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_fill_color/2","doc":"Set the color to use when filling.\n\nThis takes either a `Pdf.Color.color/1` atom, an RGB tuple or a CMYK tuple.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_fill_color/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_fill_opacity/2","doc":"Set the fill opacity (0.0 fully transparent, 1.0 fully opaque).","ref":"Pdf.html#set_fill_opacity/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_font/3","doc":"Sets the font that will be used for all text from here on.\nYou can either specify the font size, or a list of options:\n\nOption  |  Value  | Default\n:------ | :------ | :------\n`:size`   | integer | 10\n`:bold`   | boolean | false\n`:italic` | boolean | false","ref":"Pdf.html#set_font/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_font_size/2","doc":"Sets the font size.\n\nThe font has to have been previously set!","ref":"Pdf.html#set_font_size/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_info/2","doc":"Set multiple keys in the PDF information section.\n\nValid keys\n  - `:author`\n  - `:created`\n  - `:creator`\n  - `:keywords`\n  - `:modified`\n  - `:producer`\n  - `:subject`\n  - `:title`","ref":"Pdf.html#set_info/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_keywords/2","doc":"Sets the keywords in the PDF information section.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_keywords/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_line_cap/2","doc":"The line endings to draw, see `t:cap_style/0`.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_line_cap/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_line_join/2","doc":"The join style to use where lines meet, see `t:join_style/0`.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_line_join/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_line_width/2","doc":"The width to use when drawing lines.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_line_width/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_opacity/2","doc":"Set both fill and stroke opacity (0.0 fully transparent, 1.0 fully opaque).","ref":"Pdf.html#set_opacity/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_producer/2","doc":"Sets the producer in the PDF information section.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_producer/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_stroke_color/2","doc":"Set the color to use when drawing lines.\n\nThis takes either a `Pdf.Color.color/1` atom, an RGB tuple or a CMYK tuple.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_stroke_color/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_stroke_opacity/2","doc":"Set the stroke opacity (0.0 fully transparent, 1.0 fully opaque).","ref":"Pdf.html#set_stroke_opacity/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_subject/2","doc":"Sets the subject in the PDF information section.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_subject/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_text_leading/2","doc":"Leading is a typography term that describes the distance between each line of text. The name comes from a time when typesetting was done by hand and pieces of lead were used to separate the lines.\n\nToday, leading is often used synonymously with \"line height\" or \"line spacing.\"","ref":"Pdf.html#set_text_leading/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.set_title/2","doc":"Sets the title in the PDF information section.","ref":"Pdf.html#set_title/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.size/1","doc":"Returns a `{width, height}` for the current page.","ref":"Pdf.html#size/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.spacer/2","doc":"Add vertical space by moving the cursor down.","ref":"Pdf.html#spacer/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.spacer/2","doc":"pdf |> Pdf.spacer(20)","ref":"Pdf.html#spacer/2-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.stroke/1","doc":"Perform all the previous graphic commands.","ref":"Pdf.html#stroke/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.table/5","doc":"Add a table in the document at the given coordinates.\n\nSee [Tables](tables.html) for more information on how to use tables.","ref":"Pdf.html#table/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.table!/5","doc":"Add a table in the document at the given coordinates.\nRaises an exception if the table does not fit the dimensions.\n\nSee [Tables](tables.html) for more information on how to use tables.","ref":"Pdf.html#table!/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.text/3","doc":"Write styled text at the current cursor position with auto-wrapping.\nMoves the cursor down after writing.","ref":"Pdf.html#text/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.text/3","doc":"pdf |> Pdf.text(\"Hello world\")\n    pdf |> Pdf.text(\"Bold red\", %{bold: true, color: :red, font_size: 16})","ref":"Pdf.html#text/3-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.text_at/3","doc":"Writes the text at the given coordinates.\nThe coordinates are the bottom left of the text.\n\nThe _text_ can be either a binary or a list of binaries or annotated binaries.\nAll text will be drawn on the same line, no wrapping will occur, it may overrun the page.\n\nWhen given a list, you can supply a mix of binaries and annotated binaries.\nAn annotated binary is a tuple `{binary, options}`, with the options being:\n\nOption  |  Value  | Default\n:------ | :------ | :------\n`:font_size`   | integer | current\n`:bold`   | boolean | false\n`:italic` | boolean | false\n`:leading` | integer | current\n`:color` | :atom | current\n\nWhen setting `bold: true` or `italic: true`, make sure that your current font supports these or an error will occur.\nIf using an external font, you have to `add_font/2` all variants you want to use.","ref":"Pdf.html#text_at/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.text_at/4","doc":"Writes the text at the given coordinates.\nThe coordinates are the bottom left of the text.\n\nAccepts either a keyword list of options or a style map/atom:\n\n    pdf |> Pdf.text_at({300, 730}, \"BILL TO\", %{bold: true, color: :gray})\n    pdf |> Pdf.text_at({300, 730}, \"BILL TO\", :label)\n    pdf |> Pdf.text_at({300, 730}, \"BILL TO\", kerning: true)","ref":"Pdf.html#text_at/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.text_lines/4","doc":"This function draws a number of text lines starting at the given coordinates.\nThe list can overrun the page, no errors or wrapping will occur.\n\nKerning can be set, see `text_at/4` for more information.","ref":"Pdf.html#text_lines/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.text_wrap/4","doc":"Writes the text wrapped within the confines of the given dimensions.\nThe `{x,y}` is the top-left of corner of the box, for this reason it is not wise to try to match it up with `text_at` on the same line.\n\nThe y-coordinate can also be set to `:cursor`.\n\nThe text will break at whitespace, such as, space, soft-hyphen, hyphen, cr, lf,  tab, ...\n\nIf the text is too large for the box, it may overrun its boundaries, but only horizontally.\n\nThis function will return a tuple `{pid, :complete}` if all text was rendered, or `{pid, remaining}` if not.\nIt can subsequently be called with the _remaining_ data, after eg starting a new page, until `{pid, :complete}`.\n\nThe _text_ can be either a binary or a list of binaries or annotated binaries.\nThe `:kerning` option if set will apply to all rendered text.\n\nWhen given a list, you can supply a mix of binaries and annotated binaries.\nAn annotated binary is a tuple `{binary, options}`, with the options being:\n\nOption  |  Value  | Default\n:------ | :------ | :------\n`:font_size`   | integer | current\n`:bold`   | boolean | false\n`:italic` | boolean | false\n`:leading` | integer | current\n`:color` | :atom | current\n\nWhen choosing `:bold` or `:italic`, make sure that your current font supports these or an error will occur.\nIf using an external font, you have to `add_font/2` all variants you want to use.","ref":"Pdf.html#text_wrap/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.text_wrap/5","doc":"This function has the same options as `text_wrap/4`, but also supports additional options that will be applied to the complete text.\n\nOption  |  Value  | Default\n:------ | :------ | :------\n`:align` | :left , :center , :right | :left\n`:kerning` | `boolean` | false","ref":"Pdf.html#text_wrap/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.text_wrap!/4","doc":"This function has the same options as `text_wrap/4`, but if the text is too large for the box, a `RuntimeError` will be raised.","ref":"Pdf.html#text_wrap!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.text_wrap!/5","doc":"This function has the same options as `text_wrap/5`, but if the text is too large for the box, a `RuntimeError` will be raised.","ref":"Pdf.html#text_wrap!/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.transform/2","doc":"Apply an arbitrary transformation matrix {a, b, c, d, e, f}.\nMust be used within `save_state/restore_state`.","ref":"Pdf.html#transform/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.translate/2","doc":"Translate (move) the coordinate origin by {tx, ty}.\nMust be used within `save_state/restore_state`.","ref":"Pdf.html#translate/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.watermark/3","doc":"Add a text watermark to the current page with rotation and opacity.","ref":"Pdf.html#watermark/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.watermark/3","doc":"pdf |> Pdf.watermark(\"DRAFT\", %{opacity: 0.1, rotate: 45, font_size: 60, color: :gray})","ref":"Pdf.html#watermark/3-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.write_to/2","doc":"Write the PDF to the given path","ref":"Pdf.html#write_to/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Color","doc":"A list of predefined colors you can use","ref":"Pdf.Color.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Color.color/1","doc":"This functions returns the `rgb` tuple for the given color.\n\n :pink \n :light_pink \n :hot_pink \n :deep_pink \n :pale_violet_red \n :medium_violet_red \n :light_salmon \n :salmon \n :dark_salmon \n :light_coral \n :indian_red \n :crimson \n :firebrick \n :dark_red \n :red \n :orange_red \n :tomato \n :coral \n :dark_orange \n :orange \n :yellow \n :light_yellow \n :lemon_chiffon \n :light_goldenrod_yellow \n :papaya_whip \n :moccasin \n :peach_puff \n :pale_goldenrod \n :khaki \n :dark_khaki \n :gold \n :cornsilk \n :blanched_almond \n :bisque \n :navajo_white \n :wheat \n :burlywood \n :tan \n :rosy_brown \n :sandy_brown \n :goldenrod \n :dark_goldenrod \n :peru \n :chocolate \n :saddle_brown \n :sienna \n :brown \n :maroon \n :dark_olive_green \n :olive \n :olive_drab \n :yellow_green \n :lime_green \n :lime \n :lawn_green \n :chartreuse \n :green_yellow \n :spring_green \n :medium_spring_green \n :light_green \n :pale_green \n :dark_sea_green \n :medium_aquamarine \n :medium_sea_green \n :sea_green \n :forest_green \n :green \n :dark_green \n :aqua \n :cyan \n :light_cyan \n :pale_turquoise \n :aquamarine \n :turquoise \n :medium_turquoise \n :dark_turquoise \n :light_sea_green \n :cadet_blue \n :dark_cyan \n :teal \n :light_steel_blue \n :powder_blue \n :light_blue \n :sky_blue \n :light_sky_blue \n :deep_sky_blue \n :dodger_blue \n :cornflower_blue \n :steel_blue \n :royal_blue \n :blue \n :medium_blue \n :dark_blue \n :navy \n :midnight_blue \n :lavender \n :thistle \n :plum \n :violet \n :orchid \n :fuchsia \n :magenta \n :medium_orchid \n :medium_purple \n :blue_violet \n :dark_violet \n :dark_orchid \n :dark_magenta \n :purple \n :indigo \n :dark_slate_blue \n :slate_blue \n :medium_slate_blue \n :white \n :snow \n :honeydew \n :mint_cream \n :azure \n :alice_blue \n :ghost_white \n :white_smoke \n :seashell \n :beige \n :old_lace \n :floral_white \n :ivory \n :antique_white \n :linen \n :lavender_blush \n :misty_rose \n :gainsboro \n :light_gray \n :silver \n :dark_gray \n :gray \n :dim_gray \n :light_slate_gray \n :slate_gray \n :dark_slate_gray \n :black","ref":"Pdf.Color.html#color/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Box","doc":"Box component for PDF documents.\n\nRenders a rectangular container with optional padding, margin, border,\nborder_radius, and background. Operates at Document level.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Box.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Pdf.Component.Box","doc":"doc\n    |> Pdf.Component.Box.render({50, 700}, {300, 200}, %{\n      padding: 10, border: 1, border_radius: 8, background: {0.95, 0.95, 1.0}\n    }, fn doc, area ->\n      Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x + 5, area.y - 14}, \"Inside the box\")\n    end)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Box.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Box.render/5","doc":"Render a box at `{x, y}` with size `{w, h}`, applying `style` options,\nthen invoke `callback.(doc, inner_area)`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Box.html#render/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Style options - Pdf.Component.Box.render/5","doc":"- `:padding` — inner spacing (CSS shorthand: number, `{v, h}`, `{t, r, b, l}`)\n- `:margin` — outer spacing (CSS shorthand)\n- `:border` — border width (CSS shorthand)\n- `:border_color` — border color (default `:black`)\n- `:border_radius` — corner radius (default `0`)\n- `:background` — fill color (default `nil`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Box.html#render/5-style-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Column","doc":"Column component for PDF documents.\n\nStacks content vertically with fixed heights per row.\nOperates at Document level.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Column.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Pdf.Component.Column","doc":"doc\n    |> Pdf.Component.Column.render({50, 700}, {300, 400}, [\n      {50, fn doc, area -> Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Row 1\") end},\n      {80, fn doc, area -> Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Row 2\") end}\n    ], gap: 5)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Column.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Column.render/5","doc":"Render a vertical column at `{x, y}` with size `{w, h}`.\n\n`rows` is a list of `{height, callback}` tuples where each callback\nreceives `(doc, %{x, y, width, height})`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Column.html#render/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Pdf.Component.Column.render/5","doc":"- `:gap` — space between rows (default `0`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Column.html#render/5-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Component.Row","doc":"Row component for PDF documents.\n\nDistributes content horizontally in columns by weight.\nOperates at Document level.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Row.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Example - Pdf.Component.Row","doc":"doc\n    |> Pdf.Component.Row.render({50, 700}, {400, 80}, [\n      {1, fn doc, area -> Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Col 1\") end},\n      {2, fn doc, area -> Pdf.text_at(doc, {area.x, area.y - 14}, \"Col 2\") end}\n    ], gap: 10)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Row.html#module-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Component.Row.render/5","doc":"Render a horizontal row at `{x, y}` with size `{w, h}`.\n\n`columns` is a list of `{weight, callback}` tuples where each callback\nreceives `(doc, %{x, y, width, height})`.","ref":"Pdf.Component.Row.html#render/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Pdf.Component.Row.render/5","doc":"- `:gap` — space between columns (default `0`)","ref":"Pdf.Component.Row.html#render/5-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Dimension","doc":"Resolves relative dimensions against a parent reference.\n\nSupports:\n- `:full` — 100% of the parent dimension\n- `\"N%\"` — percentage of the parent dimension (e.g. `\"50%\"`)\n- `number` — absolute value (pass-through)","ref":"Pdf.Dimension.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Dimension","doc":"iex> Pdf.Dimension.resolve(:full, 400)\n    400\n\n    iex> Pdf.Dimension.resolve(\"50%\", 400)\n    200.0\n\n    iex> Pdf.Dimension.resolve(200, 400)\n    200","ref":"Pdf.Dimension.html#module-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Dimension.needs_resolution?/1","doc":"Returns `true` if either dimension in the size tuple is relative.","ref":"Pdf.Dimension.html#needs_resolution?/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Dimension.relative?/1","doc":"Returns `true` if the value is a relative dimension (`:full` or `\"N%\"`).","ref":"Pdf.Dimension.html#relative?/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Dimension.resolve/2","doc":"Resolve a single dimension value against a parent dimension.","ref":"Pdf.Dimension.html#resolve/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Dimension.resolve_size/2","doc":"Resolve a `{w, h}` size tuple against a parent area `%{width:, height:}`.\n\nReturns `{resolved_w, resolved_h}`.","ref":"Pdf.Dimension.html#resolve_size/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Layout","doc":"Layout helpers for positioning content in PDF documents.\n\nProvides `box/4`, `row/4`, and `column/4` containers that manage\ncoordinates, padding, margin, and borders based on `Pdf.Style`.","ref":"Pdf.Layout.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Layout.box/5","doc":"Render content inside a box with padding, margin, border, and optional background.\n\nThe callback receives `(page, %{x, y, width, height})` with the inner content area\n(after padding/margin are applied) and must return the updated page.","ref":"Pdf.Layout.html#box/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.Layout.box/5","doc":"Layout.box(page, {50, 700}, {200, 100}, style: %{padding: 10, border: 1}, fn page, area ->\n      Page.text_at(page, {area.x, area.y - 12}, \"Inside box\")\n    end)","ref":"Pdf.Layout.html#box/5-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Layout.column/5","doc":"Stack content vertically.\n\nTakes a list of `{height, callback}` tuples. Each item is placed\nbelow the previous one.","ref":"Pdf.Layout.html#column/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.Layout.column/5","doc":"Layout.column(page, {50, 700}, {400, 300}, [\n      {20, fn page, area -> Page.text_at(page, {area.x, area.y - 12}, \"Row 1\") end},\n      {20, fn page, area -> Page.text_at(page, {area.x, area.y - 12}, \"Row 2\") end}\n    ])","ref":"Pdf.Layout.html#column/5-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Layout.row/5","doc":"Distribute content horizontally in columns.\n\nTakes a list of `{weight, callback}` tuples. The available width is\nsplit proportionally by weight.","ref":"Pdf.Layout.html#row/5"},{"type":"function","title":"Example - Pdf.Layout.row/5","doc":"Layout.row(page, {50, 700}, {400, 100}, [\n      {1, fn page, area -> Page.text_at(page, {area.x, area.y - 12}, \"Left\") end},\n      {2, fn page, area -> Page.text_at(page, {area.x, area.y - 12}, \"Center (2x wide)\") end},\n      {1, fn page, area -> Page.text_at(page, {area.x, area.y - 12}, \"Right\") end}\n    ])","ref":"Pdf.Layout.html#row/5-example"},{"type":"module","title":"Pdf.Style","doc":"CSS-like styling system for PDF elements.\n\nStyles are maps with atom keys that can be created, merged, and resolved.\nSupports shorthand notation for padding, margin, and border (similar to CSS).","ref":"Pdf.Style.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Examples - Pdf.Style","doc":"Style.new(%{font_size: 14, color: :red, padding: 10})\n    Style.new(%{font: \"Helvetica\", bold: true, opacity: 0.5})\n    Style.merge(parent_style, child_style)","ref":"Pdf.Style.html#module-examples"},{"type":"type","title":"Pdf.Style.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Pdf.Style.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Style.expand_shorthand/1","doc":"Normalize a shorthand value into a {top, right, bottom, left} tuple.\n\nSupports CSS-like shorthand:\n- `10` → `{10, 10, 10, 10}`\n- `{5, 10}` → `{5, 10, 5, 10}`\n- `{5, 10, 15}` → `{5, 10, 15, 10}`\n- `{5, 10, 15, 20}` → `{5, 10, 15, 20}`","ref":"Pdf.Style.html#expand_shorthand/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Style.merge/2","doc":"Merge two styles. The child style overrides the parent for any non-nil fields\nexplicitly set in the child.","ref":"Pdf.Style.html#merge/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - Pdf.Style.merge/2","doc":"iex> parent = Pdf.Style.new(%{font_size: 12, color: :black})\n    iex> child = Pdf.Style.new(%{color: :red, bold: true})\n    iex> merged = Pdf.Style.merge(parent, child)\n    iex> merged.font_size\n    12\n    iex> merged.color\n    :red\n    iex> merged.bold\n    true","ref":"Pdf.Style.html#merge/2-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Style.new/1","doc":"Create a new Style from a map or keyword list.","ref":"Pdf.Style.html#new/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - Pdf.Style.new/1","doc":"iex> Pdf.Style.new(%{font_size: 14, color: :red})\n    %Pdf.Style{font_size: 14, color: :red}\n\n    iex> Pdf.Style.new(font_size: 14, padding: 10)\n    %Pdf.Style{font_size: 14, padding: {10, 10, 10, 10}}","ref":"Pdf.Style.html#new/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Pdf.Style.to_opts/1","doc":"Convert a Style struct to a keyword list suitable for passing to\nexisting Page/Document functions.","ref":"Pdf.Style.html#to_opts/1"},{"type":"extras","title":"ExPdfCore","doc":"# ExPdfCore\n\n[![Hex.pm](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/v/ex_pdf_core.svg)](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_pdf_core)\n[![Docs](https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-hexdocs-blue)](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_pdf_core)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/l/ex_pdf_core.svg)](https://github.com/MisaelMa/ExPDF/blob/main/LICENSE.md)\n\nCore PDF writer engine for Elixir — document, page, export, fonts, images,\ngraphics state, and layout primitives. Uses only the Erlang/OTP standard\nlibrary. No Hex runtime dependencies, no system tools.\n\nPart of the [ExPDF](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_pdf) umbrella.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - ExPdfCore","doc":"```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:ex_pdf_core, \"~> 1.0\"}\n  ]\nend\n```\n\n> Most users should depend on [`ex_pdf`](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_pdf)\n> instead, which bundles core, components, and the reader.","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"What's included - ExPdfCore","doc":"- **`Pdf`** — main API: build documents, add pages, draw text, images,\n  shapes, and manage graphics state\n- **`Pdf.Document`** — document structure, page tree, fonts, objects\n- **`Pdf.Page`** — individual page content streams\n- **`Pdf.Export`** — serialize to PDF binary\n- **`Pdf.Layout`** — text measurement and wrapping\n- **`Pdf.Font` / `Pdf.Fonts`** — built-in and external font handling\n- **`Pdf.Component.Box`** — box with border, background, padding\n- **`Pdf.Component.Row`** — horizontal column distribution by weight\n- **`Pdf.Component.Column`** — vertical row stacking with fixed heights","ref":"readme.html#what-s-included"},{"type":"extras","title":"Usage - ExPdfCore","doc":"```elixir\nPdf.build([size: :a4, compress: true], fn pdf ->\n  pdf\n  |> Pdf.set_font(\"Helvetica\", 12)\n  |> Pdf.text_at({200, 200}, \"Hello, world!\")\n  |> Pdf.add_image({100, 100}, \"logo.png\")\nend)\n|> Pdf.export()\n```","ref":"readme.html#usage"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - ExPdfCore","doc":"MIT. See [LICENSE.md](https://github.com/MisaelMa/ExPDF/blob/main/LICENSE.md).","ref":"readme.html#license"}],"proglang":"elixir","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.2"},"content_type":"text/markdown"}